definitions.definition: The main god of the Phoenicians . Although at one time believed to be represented as half man and half fish , modern scholarship recognizes that the latter was the apkallu , while Dagan/Dagon was a grain god.

main_definition: The main god of the Phoenicians . Although at one time believed to be represented as half man and half fish , modern scholarship recognizes that the latter was the apkallu , while Dagan/Dagon was a grain god.
